nd conversion\n24: - [ ] Verify package compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager`\n25: \n26: **Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager` to ensure the package structure is valid\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ### Task 2: Add gorilla/mux dependency\n31: - [ ] Add `github.com/gorilla/mux` to go.mod\n32:   - [ ] Run `go get github.com/gorilla/mux`\n33:   - [ ] Run `go mod tidy` to update dependencies\n34: - [ ] Verify mux is imported correctly in router.go\n35: - [ ] Test mux basic functionality with a simple route\n36: - [ ] Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager` to verify no compilation errors\n37: \n38: **Verification**: Check go.mod for mux dependency and ensure package builds successfully\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### Task 3: Implement Config structure and loading\n43: - [ ] Define Config struct in `config.go`\n44:   - [ ] `ListenAddr string` - Server listen address\n45:   - [ ] `Port int` - Server port\n46:   - [ ] `KubeConfigPath string` - Kubernetes config path\n47:   - [ ] `LogLevel string` - Logging level\n48:   - [ ] `MetricsEnabled bool` - Metrics enabled flag\n49:   - [ ] `RedisAddr string` - Redis address\n50:   - [ ] `RedisPassword string` - Redis password\n51: - [ ] Implement `LoadConfig() (*Config, error)` function\n52:   - [ ] Load from environment variables\n53:   - [ ] Load from config file (if specified)\n54:   - [ ] Apply default values for missing config\n55:   - [ ] Validate required configuration fields\n56: - [ ] Add `NewDefaultConfig() *Config` function with sensible defaults\n57:   - [ ] `ListenAddr`: \"0.0.0.0\"\n58:   - [ ] `Port`: 8080\n59:   - [ ] `LogLevel`: \"info\"\n60:   - [ ] `MetricsEnabled`: true\n61: - [ ] Create `config_test.go` with unit tests\n62:   - [ ] Test default config creation\n63:   - [ ] Test environment variable loading\n64:   - [ ] Test config file loading\n65:   - [ ] Test config validation\n66: \n67: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestConfig` to verify all config tests pass\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### Task 4: Implement error types and conversion\n72: - [ ] Define error types in `errors.go`\n73:   - [ ] `ErrorResponse struct` - Standardized error response\n74:     - [ ] `Code string` - Error code\n75:     - [ ] `Message string` - Error message\n76:     - [ ] `Details map[string]interface{}` - Additional error details\n77:   - [ ] `ErrorCode type` - Type for error codes\n78: - [ ] Define error codes\n79:   - [ ] `ErrCodeRuntimeNotFound = \"RuntimeNotFound\"`\n80:   - [ ] `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound = \"InterpreterNotFound\"`\n81:   - [ ] `ErrCodeInvalidRequest = \"InvalidRequest\"`\n82:   - [ ] `ErrCodeUnauthorized = \"Unauthorized\"`\n83:   - [ ] `ErrCodeForbidden = \"Forbidden\"`\n84:   - [ ] `ErrCodeInternalError = \"InternalError\"`\n85:   - [ ] `ErrCodeConflict = \"Conflict\"`\n86: - [ ] Implement `NewErrorResponse(code, message string) *ErrorResponse`\n87: - [ ] Implement `NewErrorResponseWithDetails(code, message string, details map[string]interface{}) *ErrorResponse`\n88: - [ ] Implement `WriteJSONError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, errResp *ErrorResponse)`\n89: - [ ] Implement `K8sErrorToHTTP(err error) (int, *ErrorResponse)`\n90:   - [ ] Handle `IsNotFound()` -> 404 RuntimeNotFound/InterpreterNotFound\n91:   - [ ] Handle `IsConflict()` -> 409 Conflict\n92:   - [ ] Handle `IsUnauthorized()` -> 401 Unauthorized\n93:   - [ ] Handle `IsForbidden()` -> 403 Forbidden\n94:   - [ ] Handle generic errors -> 500 InternalError\n95: - [ ] Create `errors_test.go` with unit tests\n96:   - [ ] Test error response creation\n97:   - [ ] Test K8s error to HTTP conversion for various error types\n98: \n99: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestError` to verify error handling tests pass\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 664. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create package structure and initialize module\n- [ ] Verify `pkg/workloadmanager` directory exists\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Server structure and lifecycle\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` - Router registration and dispatching\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware.go` - Middleware implementations\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Base handler interfaces and implementations\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/agentruntime.go` - AgentRuntime specific handlers\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/codeinterpreter.go` - CodeInterpreter specific handlers\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/health.go` - Health check endpoints\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/response.go` - Response formatting and error handling\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/config.go` - Configuration loading and management","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775842976230,"end":1775842976246}}}}
